race.description: Mcgrath Pink Race Day Women's Invitation Race Hcp
race.comment: CHIX (11) created a big impression on debut in the small field when saluting over 1250m in a Super Maiden at Beaumont (Newcastle). Massive leap in grade when dropped out sharply to run eighth over 1300m at Randwick. Was slow to recover on that occasion and since fitted with a trial placing over 1050m. Expected to return to form in this easier contest. HYDROMETER (1) goes well on his home track, and a win looks imminent. Nailed late with the 61kg when second over 1200m at Gosford. Claim helps and will push forward. KYEEMA (2) first start on his home track and will find this much easier from the inside draw. No match for Oui Oui Oui when ninth over 1400m at Randwick in Midway grade. Assess on his narrow second, first-up. Respect. EXCEED PERFECTION (17) unlucky not to have a few more wins on the CV and strips fitter today from the good gate. Solid top-three contender. FIREWORK (16) heavily supported on resumption when shedding his Maiden tag over 1200m at Gosford. Worth thought.
